  "text": "The other method of analysis is based on the correspondence principle of [CITATION_1] . This principle says that for simple free vibrations of a homogeneous medium the displacement field U(x) exp (&t) of a viscoelastic solid is related to the elastic displacement field U(x) exp (iw,f) according to the conditions that the viscoelastic vibration frequency wg and the corresponding elastic frequency we be related by the condition where K , is the complex wave velocity and K , is the corresponding real elastic wave velocity. That is, in terms of the elastic modulusM, and the density p , we have K , = d M x . Application of a correspondence principle",
